[0.094, "o", "\u001b[0;1;31m⚠️  Mount point '/boot' which backs the random seed file is world accessible, which is a security hole!  ⚠️\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b[0;1;31m⚠️ Random seed file '/boot/loader/.#bootctlrandom-seedc57f8875b5d83eb1' is world accessible, which is a security hole! ⚠️\u001b[0m\r\r\nRandom seed file /boot/loader/random-seed successfully written (32 bytes).\r\r\n\u001b[0;1;39mNot booted with EFI or running in a container, skipping EFI variable modifications.\u001b[0m\r\r\n\u001b]0;root@blackbird:/\u0007\u001b[?2004h[root@blackbird /]# "]
